39
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:45.201
Won't be out of the hyperbaric
chambers for another few days minimum.

40
00:04:45.202 --> 00:04:48.162
And that's when they'll know if
there's any long term damage.

41
00:04:48.163 --> 00:04:50.706
Been seeing more of this up
here in the last couple of weeks

42
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.000
since what happened in Moscow.

43
00:04:52.668 --> 00:04:54.253
Russian against Russian.

44
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:57.631
We can't have this.
Ed. Not up here.

45
00:05:00.008 --> 00:05:01.259
What are you saying?

46
00:05:01.260 --> 00:05:02.885
I'm pulling her wings.

47
00:05:02.886 --> 00:05:05.471
Just because he lost the fight
doesn't mean he was innocent.

48
00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:07.557
Svetlana could
have killed Galkin.

49
00:05:07.558 --> 00:05:09.141
But she didn't.

50
00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:12.478
Either way. I'm removing her
from flight status indefinitely.

51
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:14.981
Come on. Dani. You know
what flying means to her.

52
00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:19.068
Yes. But there have got to be
consequences for what she did.

53
00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:22.613
She'll be confined to the
base without pay for 60 sols.

54
00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:24.699
I think you should reconsider.

55
00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:27.743
You said it yourself. Look. she's
one of the best pilots we got.

56
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:30.872
And if you wanna stay on the
asteroid training mission schedule.

57
00:05:30.873 --> 00:05:32.039
we'll have a hell of a time

58
00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:34.208
trying to find someone else
to bring up to her level.

59
00:05:34.209 --> 00:05:35.711
I've made my decision.

60
00:05:37.546 --> 00:05:38.714
Bring her in.

61
00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:51.268
Svetlana.

62
00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:02.570
Comrade Zakharova.

63
00:06:02.571 --> 00:06:04.780
I have read the incident report.

64
00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:07.200
and I've come to a decision
about your punishment.

65
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:08.577
It's irrelevant.

66
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:10.621
What do you mean?

67
00:06:11.788 --> 00:06:15.959
I've just heard from Star City.
I've been recalled to Moscow.

68
00:06:17.336 --> 00:06:19.463
I am to go home on Unity.

69
00:06:23.175 --> 00:06:25.302
Unity leaves tomorrow.

70
00:06:27.554 --> 00:06:28.930
Why?

71
00:06:28.931 --> 00:06:34.310
I'm to stand trial for assault and
crimes against a patriot of Soviet Union.

72
00:06:34.311 --> 00:06:36.312
But... Wait. That
doesn't make sense.

73
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:39.483
The Soviets have never recalled a
cosmonaut for something like this before.

74
00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:43.195
Vasily's family is
connected to the new regime.

75
00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:55.665
{\an8}<i>And with what we've all been
hearing about political retribution</i>

76
00:06:55.666 --> 00:06:57.417
{\an8}<i>under this new
Soviet government.</i>

77
00:06:58.168 --> 00:07:01.838
<i>I just don't feel like I can agree to
send her back under these circumstances.</i>

78
00:07:01.839 --> 00:07:03.506
<i>As the Commander
of Happy Valley.</i>

79
00:07:03.507 --> 00:07:06.718
<i>my first priority is to
the safety of this crew.</i>

80
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:11.764
Well. I gotta say I'm with
Commander Poole on this one.

81
00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:14.560
We can't just stand back while
they ship her to some gulag.

82
00:07:15.060 --> 00:07:17.270
I hear you. Will. I do. But...

83
00:07:17.271 --> 00:07:19.730
where this gets tricky
is with the M-7 Charter

84
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:22.400
that President Wilson
negotiated with Gorbachev.

85
00:07:22.401 --> 00:07:23.776
It says it pretty clear.

86
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:27.321
Any nation that desires to recall
one of its citizens from Mars.

87
00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:28.781
it's within their rights.

88
00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:31.534
So we're just gonna kowtow
to this... this lunatic?

89
00:07:31.535 --> 00:07:33.745
No one said anything
about kowtowing.

90
00:07:34.371 --> 00:07:36.540
The president wants to
stand up for what's right.

91
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:40.294
But history is not made by talking with
only the people that agree with you.

92
00:07:42.546 --> 00:07:44.922
Now tell us more about
this new head of Roscosmos.

93
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.967
So I know who we're
dealing with here.

94
00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:50.636
Irina Morozova.

95
00:07:50.637 --> 00:07:52.138
From what little
we know about her.

96
00:07:52.139 --> 00:07:54.891
she's been in the security
and surveillance apparatus

97
00:07:54.892 --> 00:07:57.018
at Star City since '69.

98
00:07:57.019 --> 00:07:59.228
From an elite Russian
family in Moscow.

99
00:07:59.229 --> 00:08:02.481
She seemed to have fallen out of
favor with the Gorbachev regime.

100
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:06.861
as did much of the KGB. which. we
think. is why she backed Korzhenko.

101
00:08:06.862 --> 00:08:11.157
We've been getting reports that she's
been slowly purging Roscosmos of those

102
00:08:11.158 --> 00:08:12.950
thought to be disloyal
to the new regime.

103
00:08:12.951 --> 00:08:15.995
And it looks like she's settling
scores up on Mars now too.

104
00:08:15.996 --> 00:08:19.665
Cosmonaut Zakharova was an
outspoken supporter of Gorbachev.

105
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:23.211
Well. I'm sure a
compromise can be found.

106
00:08:23.212 --> 00:08:27.257
If I can hash out a good deal with
the UAW. I guarantee I can with her.

107
00:08:29.218 --> 00:08:30.719
I like working
with the Russians.

108
00:08:32.054 --> 00:08:33.347
They're direct.

109
00:08:34.472 --> 00:08:36.183
{\an8}They don't like beating
around the bush.

110
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:39.520
We'll just have to talk it out.

111
00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:46.693
Here is the underwear for Libes.

112
00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:50.071
dental floss for Crouse.

113
00:08:50.072 --> 00:08:51.989
socks for Halotek.

114
00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:53.617
- Here we go.
- Okay.

115
00:08:54.284 --> 00:08:56.118
I got some more orders.

116
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:58.372
David Markman wants
more beef jerky.

117
00:08:59.289 --> 00:09:01.583
And Reilly wants more porn.

118
00:09:02.543 --> 00:09:05.087
These are his preferred genres.

119
00:09:05.587 --> 00:09:08.297
Reilly. he is a sick fuck.

120
00:09:08.298 --> 00:09:10.092
A sick fuck with money.

121
00:09:10.676 --> 00:09:12.260
My favorite kind.

122
00:09:12.261 --> 00:09:14.637
And Lee gave me the next
order for the North Koreans.

123
00:09:14.638 --> 00:09:19.600
They want more fungal cream. more
energy bars. more Fruit of the Loom.

124
00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:21.812
This North Korean
market. Milosh.

125
00:09:22.646 --> 00:09:24.356
This is a gold mine.

126
00:09:26.149 --> 00:09:29.318
Speaking of which. any word
on that special request?

127
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.195
Our North Korean
friend was asking.

128
00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:35.075
My associate is working on
it. Tell Lee to be patient.

129
00:09:38.036 --> 00:09:39.036
Your...

130
00:09:39.037 --> 00:09:41.455
Your associate. how long
have you worked with him?

131
00:09:41.456 --> 00:09:43.833
Many years. He is friend.

132
00:09:43.834 --> 00:09:48.171
We worked together on
Moon. Now he is Earthside.

133
00:09:48.172 --> 00:09:51.800
And your associate. would he be
interested in other business ventures?

134
00:09:52.301 --> 00:09:55.387
I mean. like. if we found something
up here that we could sell down there?

135
00:09:56.597 --> 00:10:00.099
What could people on Earth
want from this wasteland?

136
00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:03.561
Well. I sent my
daughter a Mars rock.

137
00:10:03.562 --> 00:10:05.313
Well. Sam found it
for me. actually.

138
00:10:05.314 --> 00:10:11.068
but it's like a really
rare volcanic glass.

139
00:10:11.069 --> 00:10:12.154
A rock?

140
00:10:13.488 --> 00:10:14.822
Here. Just listen.

141
00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:19.494
<i>She loved the rock you sent
her. but don't get mad.</i>

142
00:10:20.037 --> 00:10:21.370
<i>Okay. we were at the Galleria</i>

143
00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:24.749
<i>and I was just browsing for a new
pair of earrings and. you know...</i>

144
00:10:24.750 --> 00:10:28.127
<i>Of course. Lily was playing with
her favorite new shiny red rock.</i>

145
00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:31.339
<i>And the owner of the jewelry
store started asking me</i>

146
00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:33.592
<i>about where the thing came from.</i>

147
00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:35.927
<i>Well. I told her.</i>

148
00:10:35.928 --> 00:10:40.891
<i>And. get this. she offered me
five grand for it on the spot.</i>

149
00:10:42.059 --> 00:10:44.477
<i>She's... She's gonna
make jewelry out of it.</i>

150
00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:47.147
<i>and she wants more.</i>

151
00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:51.817
I'm thinking if your guy
could get it to Amanda.

152
00:10:51.818 --> 00:10:54.279
this could be a big opportunity.

153
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:58.908
So now we are
import-export. huh?

154
00:10:58.909 --> 00:11:00.034
Why not?

155
00:11:00.035 --> 00:11:03.080
No. Milosh. this
is not what we do.

156
00:11:04.331 --> 00:11:08.292
I have system. Same
system for years.

157
00:11:08.293 --> 00:11:10.628
Ilya. she made five grand
off a couple ounces.

158
00:11:10.629 --> 00:11:12.672
I'm talking about it's
rare even up here.

159
00:11:12.673 --> 00:11:14.590
Could you imagine what
we could do with that?

160
00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:17.802
No. we have to be
careful. You understand?

161
00:11:17.803 --> 00:11:20.721
Start sending things down.
we'd need more people.

162
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:23.057
More people means more risk.

163
00:11:23.058 --> 00:11:26.520
More mouths to feed.
More ways to get fucked.

164
00:11:27.062 --> 00:11:30.857
My way is the best way.
Milosh. You understand?

165
00:11:30.858 --> 00:11:31.984
Yeah. I understand.

166
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:36.988
{\an8}<i>And it is my sincere hope</i>

167
00:11:36.989 --> 00:11:40.366
that the two of us can find a
reasonable solution to this situation

168
00:11:40.367 --> 00:11:42.703
that is acceptable
to both our nations.

169
00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:44.871
We are partners after all.

170
00:11:44.872 --> 00:11:46.080
<i>Indeed. we are.</i>

171
00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:48.666
As partners. we appreciate
your cooperation

172
00:11:48.667 --> 00:11:52.838
in returning Svetlana Zakharova to
the Soviet Union to face justice.

173
00:11:54.006 --> 00:11:56.048
<i>Look. it was just a
little dustup. That's all.</i>

174
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:57.216
<i>Tempers ran hot.</i>

175
00:11:57.217 --> 00:12:00.928
<i>They're under a lot of pressure to get
the asteroid program up and running.</i>

176
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:04.390
And from what I'm being
told. Galkin is on the mend.

177
00:12:04.391 --> 00:12:07.560
So this really would be best
handled by Commander Poole in situ.

178
00:12:07.561 --> 00:12:09.730
<i>It is not a question
of his recovery.</i>

179
00:12:10.689 --> 00:12:14.234
Cosmonaut Zakharova broke Soviet
law. Administrator Hobson.

180
00:12:16.195 --> 00:12:19.947
At any rate. the Happy Valley
Commander is on top of the situation.

181
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:24.160
Our charter clearly states that no
individual member of the M-7 has authority

182
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:25.913
over base disciplinary action.

183
00:12:26.496 --> 00:12:28.372
That is in the purview
of the base commander.

184
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:30.667
<i>But this doesn't fall
under base discipline.</i>

185
00:12:31.293 --> 00:12:36.339
As I said. this is about
enforcement of law. Soviet Law.

186
00:12:36.340 --> 00:12:41.428
<i>Zakharova's a Soviet citizen and
she assaulted a Soviet citizen.</i>

187
00:12:42.346 --> 00:12:44.680
<i>And the M-7 Charter
also clearly stated</i>

188
00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:48.936
we have the right to recall any
Soviets from Mars at our discretion.

189
00:12:50.187 --> 00:12:52.648
A right we now wish to exercise.

190
00:12:54.608 --> 00:12:57.819
Well. that's the
tricky thing. Irina.

191
00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:03.242
As you know. that agreement was made
when Gorbachev was head of the USSR.

192
00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:09.080
but now with your recent change of
government that you've all experienced...

193
00:13:09.081 --> 00:13:10.581
<i>Am I also to understand that</i>

194
00:13:10.582 --> 00:13:13.459
<i>once Albert Gore became
president of the United States.</i>

195
00:13:13.460 --> 00:13:17.589
all of President Ellen Wilson's
treaties become invalidated?

196
00:13:21.927 --> 00:13:23.220
That...

197
00:13:23.846 --> 00:13:25.138
It is not the same thing.

198
00:13:25.722 --> 00:13:26.723
<i>At all.</i>

199
00:13:27.891 --> 00:13:29.684
Why don't we just cut
to the chase here. okay?

200
00:13:29.685 --> 00:13:31.435
You are insisting
on this because

201
00:13:31.436 --> 00:13:35.356
Vasily Galkin's uncle has
close ties to your new premier.

202
00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:38.609
Propaganda spread by opponents
of the new government.

203
00:13:38.610 --> 00:13:41.112
Galkin's family has
no bearing on this.

204
00:13:41.113 --> 00:13:43.448
As it would have none in
your system of justice.

205
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:49.829
The simple fact is the United States
is not going to sanction this transfer.

206
00:13:49.830 --> 00:13:51.372
If you don't agree to abide

207
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:55.127
by the terms we have all
agreed to in the Charter.

208
00:13:55.836 --> 00:13:59.882
<i>then we will be forced to
reconsider participation in the M-7.</i>

209
00:14:11.185 --> 00:14:13.061
Well. that didn't
go well. did it?

210
00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:30.037
Good day. everyone.

211
00:14:31.163 --> 00:14:33.707
There is much to discuss.

212
00:14:35.167 --> 00:14:36.877
Let's begin.

213
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.047
First order of business.

214
00:14:42.633 --> 00:14:44.884
The Americans have
chosen to disregard

215
00:14:44.885 --> 00:14:47.261
the terms of the Mars Treaty

216
00:14:47.262 --> 00:14:51.307
and are refusing to send
Cosmonaut Zakharova back

217
00:14:51.308 --> 00:14:54.644
to face justice for her
aggression against the nephew

218
00:14:54.645 --> 00:14:58.397
of a highly respected
member of the new politburo.

219
00:14:58.398 --> 00:15:02.735
We must resist
this egregious act.

220
00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:04.237
Our response is in progress.

221
00:15:04.238 --> 00:15:07.031
They will face consequences
for this course of action.

222
00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:08.407
Director...

223
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:12.329
it may be wise to
reconsider this position.

224
00:15:12.913 --> 00:15:15.873
If we hope to reactivate
the asteroid program

225
00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:17.960
Zakharova should
remain at her post.

226
00:15:19.336 --> 00:15:21.337
Are you suggesting
that Zakharova

227
00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:23.881
did not. in fact.
attack Vasily Galkin?

228
00:15:23.882 --> 00:15:25.716
No. I am...

229
00:15:25.717 --> 00:15:29.054
If you were stabbed in
the back. Comrade Babanin.

230
00:15:29.721 --> 00:15:31.974
would you hand the dagger
back to your assailant?

231
00:15:35.102 --> 00:15:37.813
No. of course not.

232
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.523
I did not think so.

233
00:15:40.524 --> 00:15:45.111
We must find out if we can
once again trust the Americans.

234
00:15:45.112 --> 00:15:46.404
To this end.

235
00:15:46.405 --> 00:15:50.199
there will be no reactivation
of the asteroid program

236
00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:54.579
until we know what went wrong
with the Kronos mission.

237
00:15:54.580 --> 00:15:58.041
A tragedy that took the life of
our beloved Comrade Kuznetsov.

238
00:15:58.834 --> 00:16:01.544
Comrade Semenov. you have
the preliminary draft of

239
00:16:01.545 --> 00:16:06.048
the XF Kronos asteroid capture
accident investigation ready for us?

240
00:16:06.049 --> 00:16:07.133
Yes.

241
00:16:07.134 --> 00:16:09.760
Comrade Volkova. would you mind
handing them out for me. please?

242
00:16:09.761 --> 00:16:10.846
Immediately. Comrade.

243
00:16:20.272 --> 00:16:23.358
Please give one to
Margaret Reynolds as well.

244
00:16:24.693 --> 00:16:26.904
I want her to
review the findings.

245
00:16:28.071 --> 00:16:30.531
My apologies. we only
made enough for...

246
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:32.409
You can give her Babanin's copy.

247
00:16:35.037 --> 00:16:37.331
Comrade Semenov.
please continue.

248
00:16:38.207 --> 00:16:41.000
The American design was flawed.

249
00:16:41.001 --> 00:16:45.129
The problem was caused by an
underdamped harmonic oscillation.

250
00:16:45.130 --> 00:16:49.675
induced by the spacecraft
altitude control system.

251
00:16:49.676 --> 00:16:53.931
Altitude control thruster
firings on Ranger-1 excited...

252
00:17:46.942 --> 00:17:48.943
Commander Poole's
protecting her.

253
00:17:48.944 --> 00:17:51.821
And she's just walking around
up there like nothing happened.

254
00:17:51.822 --> 00:17:53.364
Yukking it up with the XO.

255
00:17:53.365 --> 00:17:55.867
And I heard that Vasily
might be paralyzed too.

256
00:17:55.868 --> 00:17:56.993
Brain dead.

257
00:17:56.994 --> 00:17:59.329
- That's what Manush told me.
- Really?

258
00:17:59.913 --> 00:18:01.789
A cool 20 says Vasily
gets sent home.

259
00:18:01.790 --> 00:18:03.791
and the cosmonaut gets
a slap on the wrist.

260
00:18:03.792 --> 00:18:06.419
No. You really think that?

261
00:18:06.420 --> 00:18:09.839
We gotta spell it out for you? Svetlana.
she's... she's an anointed one.

262
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.925
She's a cosmonaut. And Vasily.
he's just a peasant like us.

263
00:18:12.926 --> 00:18:15.761
I can guarantee you it would
be a very different story

264
00:18:15.762 --> 00:18:18.264
if one of us sends one
of them to the hospital.

265
00:18:18.265 --> 00:18:19.724
- No.
- Very different.

266
00:18:19.725 --> 00:18:22.686
Guys. I mean. Vasily
is kind of an asshole.

267
00:18:24.146 --> 00:18:26.606
What? I mean. you know
it's true. You know it.

268
00:18:26.607 --> 00:18:27.899
And that makes it okay?

269
00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:29.317
What... No. okay.
I'm not saying...

270
00:18:29.318 --> 00:18:33.529
No. the truth is they don't give a
shit if one of us gets hurt or worse.

271
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:36.408
Hey. Sam. You got a second?

272
00:18:37.117 --> 00:18:38.284
Yeah.

273
00:18:38.285 --> 00:18:40.329
It's too much. It's gotta stop.

274
00:18:41.163 --> 00:18:42.997
I'm telling you.
that's how it goes.

275
00:18:42.998 --> 00:18:46.251
That obsidian rock. You
remember where you found it?

276
00:18:47.169 --> 00:18:50.130
Yeah. Yeah. It was
by Peckinpah Mesa.

277
00:18:50.714 --> 00:18:51.923
There were a bunch there.

278
00:18:51.924 --> 00:18:54.050
Would you mind taking
me out tomorrow morning?

279
00:18:54.051 --> 00:18:56.845
I think I can sell them back
on Earth. I'll give you a cut.

280
00:18:59.431 --> 00:19:02.016
How can you be thinking about
selling fucking rocks right now

281
00:19:02.017 --> 00:19:04.227
when Vasily's laying in
a hyperbaric chamber?

282
00:19:04.228 --> 00:19:06.270
There's nothing we can
do about that right now.

283
00:19:06.271 --> 00:19:09.440
except not play by those
motherfuckers' rules.

284
00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:12.735
So this is about justice. not
about filling your pockets?

285
00:19:12.736 --> 00:19:14.862
Why can't it be about both?

286
00:19:14.863 --> 00:19:17.156
Come on. I cut a deal
with the suit soop

287
00:19:17.157 --> 00:19:19.659
and he's gonna let me skip the
line and get a pressure suit.

288
00:19:19.660 --> 00:19:21.578
I don't have rover
access and you do.

289
00:19:24.498 --> 00:19:25.541
So you in?

290
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:29.044
No.

291
00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:31.129
Fine. I'll hoof it.

292
00:20:45.037 --> 00:20:46.038
Damn it.

293
00:20:49.291 --> 00:20:50.292
Wait.

294
00:20:55.339 --> 00:20:56.340
May I?

295
00:21:26.745 --> 00:21:28.330
Same diameter and weight.

296
00:21:32.209 --> 00:21:33.210
Clever.

297
00:21:33.794 --> 00:21:35.963
If only the coffee
were worth the effort.

298
00:21:36.505 --> 00:21:38.549
I'll take anything
right about now.

299
00:21:41.343 --> 00:21:42.344
Thank you.

300
00:22:17.045 --> 00:22:21.383
Are these spin vector calculations for
the new asteroid capture protocols?

301
00:22:23.343 --> 00:22:24.595
Yes.

302
00:22:25.596 --> 00:22:26.596
Yes. and I admit

303
00:22:26.597 --> 00:22:30.434
I'm unable to get the finite element
model to replicate consistently.

304
00:22:31.852 --> 00:22:32.936
May I?

305
00:22:50.204 --> 00:22:52.121
If you switch reference frames.

306
00:22:52.122 --> 00:22:55.375
you might have better luck
with inverting the matrices.

307
00:22:58.921 --> 00:22:59.922
Thank you.

308
00:23:00.672 --> 00:23:01.673
We're even.

309
00:23:06.136 --> 00:23:07.846
Tatyana Alexandrovna Volkova.

310
00:23:11.433 --> 00:23:13.351
I'm Margaret.

311
00:23:13.352 --> 00:23:16.396
I know. We all know who you are.

312
00:23:18.774 --> 00:23:21.234
No one even so much
as says. "Hello."

313
00:23:21.235 --> 00:23:22.736
Director Morozova...

314
00:23:25.572 --> 00:23:29.243
Well. she made it very clear
that. we should keep our distance.

315
00:23:33.247 --> 00:23:35.082
So why did you help me just now?

316
00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:39.086
Well. a woman without
coffee is a dangerous woman.

317
00:23:43.507 --> 00:23:44.925
Very true.

318
00:24:00.524 --> 00:24:01.525
Good night.

319
00:24:03.193 --> 00:24:04.778
Good night. Ms. Reynolds.

320
00:24:12.452 --> 00:24:14.495
Have you tried rebooting
the primary root server?

321
00:24:14.496 --> 00:24:17.374
Twice. Also tried cycling
the CPU processors.

322
00:24:17.916 --> 00:24:19.751
Zilch. It's still
all in Cyrillic.

323
00:24:24.089 --> 00:24:25.090
Be right back.

324
00:24:29.011 --> 00:24:32.513
Yevgeniy. you know what's going
on with the user interface?

325
00:24:32.514 --> 00:24:33.931
It's all in Cyrillic.

326
00:24:33.932 --> 00:24:37.393
Yes. Roscosmos decided to
revert Ops computer system

327
00:24:37.394 --> 00:24:39.979
back to original
Soviet parameters.

328
00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:43.317
What? That is going to
severely disrupt operations.

329
00:24:43.942 --> 00:24:46.402
As the commander of this base.
any changes need to be run...

330
00:24:46.403 --> 00:24:49.156
Soviet Union no longer recognizes
your role as commander.

331
00:24:50.324 --> 00:24:51.950
You can't be serious.

332
00:24:52.951 --> 00:24:53.952
I'm sorry.

333
00:24:57.956 --> 00:24:59.832
Son of a bitch.

334
00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:03.044
I mean. I thought we were
beyond all this bullshit.

335
00:25:03.045 --> 00:25:06.589
It looks like all the other Soviet-aligned
countries are backing their play.

336
00:25:06.590 --> 00:25:10.511
ESA. JAXA are still with us.
ISRO's playing it coy as usual.

337
00:25:12.846 --> 00:25:14.889
What's Houston got to
say about all this?

338
00:25:14.890 --> 00:25:18.935
Well. Hobson's getting into it with
Moscow. but it's not looking good.

339
00:25:18.936 --> 00:25:22.981
They're digging in their heels. They
still want Svetlana sent back to Earth.

340
00:25:24.775 --> 00:25:27.777
Wish Kuz was here. He wouldn't
have put up with any of this shit.

341
00:25:27.778 --> 00:25:29.530
Yeah. you got that right.

342
00:25:30.280 --> 00:25:33.658
I doubt this is over. so I want
you all to do safety checks.

343
00:25:33.659 --> 00:25:37.828
Then run full diagnostics on all
your equipment. your stations.

344
00:25:37.829 --> 00:25:39.789
make sure everything's
still in working order.

345
00:25:39.790 --> 00:25:43.084
Palmer. let's do a security
sweep of the entire base.

346
00:25:43.085 --> 00:25:44.919
Make sure they're not
up to something else.

347
00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:48.589
And I want to put someone outside of
Svetlana Zakharova's quarters immediately

348
00:25:48.590 --> 00:25:50.676
to make sure the Soviets
don't try and grab her.

349
00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:52.468
Good idea.

350
00:25:52.469 --> 00:25:54.637
All right. you've all
got your marching orders.

351
00:25:54.638 --> 00:25:56.681
Let's meet back
here in two hours.

352
00:25:56.682 --> 00:25:58.058
All right.

353
00:26:07.025 --> 00:26:09.235
<i>How is this even possible. Eli?</i>

354
00:26:09.236 --> 00:26:10.153
Well. sir. I...

355
00:26:10.154 --> 00:26:13.614
<i>A month ago. Happy Valley was a
beacon of international cooperation.</i>

356
00:26:13.615 --> 00:26:16.200
<i>And now it's the front
line of a new Cold War.</i>

357
00:26:16.201 --> 00:26:20.830
Mr. President. Al. I'm working on it.
but this new director of Roscosmos...

358
00:26:20.831 --> 00:26:23.165
<i>You remember my speech
in Chicago. don't you?</i>

359
00:26:23.166 --> 00:26:25.459
<i>I said the Cold War was over.</i>

360
00:26:25.460 --> 00:26:28.337
<i>You think they're not going to play
that on repeat until election day?</i>

361
00:26:28.338 --> 00:26:31.300
That is not gonna happen. sir.
I am going to resolve this.

362
00:26:31.925 --> 00:26:33.050
<i>See that you do.</i>

363
00:26:33.051 --> 00:26:34.136
And may I...

364
00:26:41.935 --> 00:26:45.188
<i>The future of the M-7 alliance
is being called into question</i>

365
00:26:45.189 --> 00:26:47.148
{\an8}<i>in the wake of a
diplomatic crisis</i>

366
00:26:47.149 --> 00:26:51.068
{\an8}<i>over the legal status of
Cosmonaut Svetlana Zakharova.</i>

367
00:26:51.069 --> 00:26:55.740
{\an8}<i>International cooperation has been a
hallmark of the Mars colony to this point.</i>

368
00:26:55.741 --> 00:26:57.491
{\an8}<i>But that seems to
have evaporated</i>

369
00:26:57.492 --> 00:27:02.747
{\an8}<i>as several M-7 nations are refusing to
back the Gore administration's efforts</i>

370
00:27:02.748 --> 00:27:06.876
{\an8}<i>to protect Zakharova from
reprisals by the new Soviet regime.</i>

371
00:27:06.877 --> 00:27:08.878
{\an8}<i>The growing conflict
has fueled concerns</i>

372
00:27:08.879 --> 00:27:12.381
{\an8}<i>that this may reignite tensions
between the two superpowers</i>

373
00:27:12.382 --> 00:27:15.635
{\an8}<i>for the first time
since the early 1990s.</i>

374
00:27:15.636 --> 00:27:17.721
{\an8}<i>Because of what is at stake.</i>

375
00:27:18.472 --> 00:27:21.308
{\an8}<i>this matter must be
resolved expeditiously.</i>

376
00:27:22.226 --> 00:27:25.020
{\an8}<i>but deliberately and without
any rush to judgment.</i>

377
00:27:25.771 --> 00:27:28.648
{\an8}<i>This is the question
that's on everybody's mind.</i>

378
00:27:28.649 --> 00:27:31.275
{\an8}<i>Are you worried about how
the current diplomatic crisis</i>

379
00:27:31.276 --> 00:27:33.986
{\an8}<i>between the United States
and the Soviet Union</i>

380
00:27:33.987 --> 00:27:36.698
<i>will impact Helios's
financial position?</i>

381
00:27:37.407 --> 00:27:41.118
<i>Not at all. Helios is a
multinational corporation.</i>

382
00:27:41.119 --> 00:27:43.413
- We don't have a dog in this fight.
- Shaw.

383
00:27:43.997 --> 00:27:45.749
You got my suit
and camera ready?

384
00:27:46.625 --> 00:27:47.835
Pretty cool. huh?

385
00:27:48.585 --> 00:27:50.795
Dev Ayesa back in charge.

386
00:27:50.796 --> 00:27:52.880
Can't wait till he kicks
some ass down there.

387
00:27:52.881 --> 00:27:54.173
Yeah. fuck that guy.

388
00:27:54.174 --> 00:27:55.800
What's your beef with Dev?

389
00:27:55.801 --> 00:27:58.011
Man. he put a lot of
people I know out of work.

390
00:27:58.512 --> 00:28:00.472
Mr. Buzzkill over here.

391
00:28:01.932 --> 00:28:04.350
Here's your camera
and cooling garment.

392
00:28:04.351 --> 00:28:05.811
I'll bring your suit out to you.

393
00:28:07.646 --> 00:28:09.731
Store your shit in one of
those lockers over there.

394
00:28:12.359 --> 00:28:15.695
<i>'cause Helios is a service company.
I'm here to change all that.</i>

395
00:28:15.696 --> 00:28:17.864
<i>To get back to the
original vision.</i>

396
00:28:17.865 --> 00:28:20.032
{\an8}<i>Building a thriving
colony on Mars.</i>

397
00:28:20.033 --> 00:28:21.869
{\an8}<i>Not just for astronauts
and scientists.</i>

398
00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:25.289
{\an8}<i>but for anyone who wants
to make the journey.</i>

399
00:28:30.127 --> 00:28:31.461
Hey. how you doing?

400
00:28:32.629 --> 00:28:34.339
My first time out
on the surface.

401
00:28:35.674 --> 00:28:38.635
I'm gonna take some
pictures for the kiddos.

402
00:28:48.478 --> 00:28:50.105
And here's your suit.

403
00:28:59.072 --> 00:29:00.616
Can I get one of those suits?

404
00:29:01.617 --> 00:29:02.868
They're all booked.

405
00:29:03.952 --> 00:29:07.372
If you want to get out there today.
this is the only one I got available.

406
00:29:15.464 --> 00:29:17.007
You gotta key your radio.

407
00:29:18.425 --> 00:29:20.135
Is it supposed to
smell like this?

408
00:29:34.816 --> 00:29:36.610
They're on that mesa. pilgrim.

409
00:29:38.237 --> 00:29:40.405
They've been following
us for two days.

410
00:29:41.240 --> 00:29:43.992
Only one tribe wears a
war bonnet like that.

411
00:29:44.576 --> 00:29:46.577
Noyuhka Comanche.

412
00:29:46.578 --> 00:29:47.913
Don't look. you fool!

413
00:29:58.757 --> 00:30:00.259
Where the hell are these things?

414
00:30:01.301 --> 00:30:03.011
This is where Sam
said they'd be.

415
00:30:26.577 --> 00:30:29.246
Bingo.

416
00:31:41.652 --> 00:31:42.693
Goddamn it!

417
00:31:42.694 --> 00:31:43.779
Fuck!

418
00:31:46.698 --> 00:31:48.951
Oh. man!

419
00:32:01.088 --> 00:32:02.214
Commander Poole?

420
00:32:03.382 --> 00:32:04.925
Sorry to bother you...

421
00:32:05.551 --> 00:32:06.926
What's on your mind?

422
00:32:06.927 --> 00:32:08.011
Well...

423
00:32:10.097 --> 00:32:11.640
Ma'am. downstairs. we're...

424
00:32:12.891 --> 00:32:16.478
concerned about the way you dealt
with-with Svetlana Zakharova.

425
00:32:18.146 --> 00:32:19.188
Who's we?

426
00:32:19.189 --> 00:32:20.899
Some of us Helios workers.

427
00:32:21.942 --> 00:32:23.901
Look. Vasily was our colleague

428
00:32:23.902 --> 00:32:26.404
and we feel like the punishment
cosmonaut Zakharova receives

429
00:32:26.405 --> 00:32:27.697
should be more appropriate.

430
00:32:27.698 --> 00:32:31.159
How do you know what her
punishment's gonna be?

431
00:32:31.743 --> 00:32:34.412
Well. we heard that you might
not be sending her back.

432
00:32:34.413 --> 00:32:35.539
You heard?

433
00:32:36.456 --> 00:32:37.582
I see.

434
00:32:37.583 --> 00:32:38.667
Right.

435
00:32:39.585 --> 00:32:42.378
Well. I talked to
everybody who was there.

436
00:32:42.379 --> 00:32:45.716
and you have no idea how
complicated the situation is.

437
00:32:47.759 --> 00:32:50.720
- Now. if you'll. excuse me...
- She put him in a hyperbaric chamber.

438
00:32:50.721 --> 00:32:54.140
I mean. the nitrogen in his blood could
lead to a stroke. paralysis or worse.

439
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:56.560
And she's just walking around
as if it's another day?

440
00:32:57.895 --> 00:32:59.062
It's not right.

441
00:33:00.147 --> 00:33:01.565
You know it's not right.

442
00:33:28.175 --> 00:33:29.510
How's he progressing. doc?

443
00:33:30.636 --> 00:33:34.097
Arterial gas embolism
is the main concern.

444
00:33:35.265 --> 00:33:36.517
No way to predict.

445
00:33:37.809 --> 00:33:40.479
But he is strong. We can hope.

446
00:33:41.438 --> 00:33:43.190
What do you think
of all this mess?

447
00:33:45.025 --> 00:33:48.403
You and I. we've
been through worse.

448
00:34:04.461 --> 00:34:06.254
Hey. where's Miles?

449
00:34:06.255 --> 00:34:08.714
We gotta get the obsidian into
the hopper cargo before launch.

450
00:34:08.715 --> 00:34:10.091
How should I know. Rich?

451
00:34:10.092 --> 00:34:11.510
Thought you went with him.

452
00:34:12.010 --> 00:34:13.762
No. no. he...

453
00:34:14.888 --> 00:34:16.723
He asked me but I said no.

454
00:34:18.183 --> 00:34:19.768
He should have been back by now.

455
00:34:22.020 --> 00:34:23.772
It's been almost five hours.

456
00:34:27.192 --> 00:34:28.360
We need to go find him.

457
00:34:31.154 --> 00:34:32.906
Miles. Sam. Do you read?

458
00:34:34.658 --> 00:34:36.952
Miles. Samantha.
do you read? Over.

459
00:34:42.123 --> 00:34:45.834
Waters. rover 7. I'm arriving
at Peckinpah Mesa now.

460
00:34:45.835 --> 00:34:48.589
- I think I see where he was headed.
- Copy that.

461
00:35:16.491 --> 00:35:20.454
No. no. no. No. no.

462
00:35:30.506 --> 00:35:33.132
Thank God. Miles?
Miles. are you okay?

463
00:35:33.133 --> 00:35:35.677
Miles. Miles. Miles!

464
00:36:01.870 --> 00:36:05.706
Sam. you found me. You found me.

465
00:36:05.707 --> 00:36:09.545
Thank God. Thank God. You
gotta get me out of here. Sam.

466
00:36:13.090 --> 00:36:14.091
What happened?

467
00:36:17.928 --> 00:36:21.932
Can you hear me? How the
hell did you get down there?

468
00:36:24.768 --> 00:36:27.980
Radio must be busted. Hang on.
I'm gonna get you out of there.

469
00:37:06.643 --> 00:37:11.355
I fell and I think I
gashed my arm when I fell.

470
00:37:11.356 --> 00:37:12.940
Thank you for coming to get me.

471
00:37:12.941 --> 00:37:14.442
You fucking asshole!

472
00:37:14.443 --> 00:37:16.444
- What the fuck is wrong with you?
- Sam!

473
00:37:16.445 --> 00:37:19.238
That tank in the Helios suit is
the only reason you're not dead!

474
00:37:19.239 --> 00:37:21.532
- Sam. relax!
- What the fuck is wrong with you?

475
00:37:21.533 --> 00:37:23.327
Sam. Sam. calm down.

476
00:37:33.629 --> 00:37:34.630
Hold still.

477
00:37:40.719 --> 00:37:41.970
Take it easy.

478
00:37:53.065 --> 00:37:54.441
Okay. all done.

479
00:37:56.109 --> 00:37:57.110
Thanks.

480
00:38:08.413 --> 00:38:12.709
<i>Rover 7. Waters. come in. Have
you located Miles? Come in.</i>

481
